##Doctors and patients in Shaoxing Exchange respect for photos, hospital response: 3-year-old boy not forced to bow

The photo was widely discussed online in the early 20th century because of its resemblance to a photograph of Mei Tenggen, the director of Hangzhou Guangji Hospital (now the Second Affiliated Hospital of Zhejiang University Medical College) , bowing to a patient, also known as "across the hundred years, " the doctor-patient mutual respect photos.

“

The photo was widely discussed online in the early 20th century because of its resemblance to a photograph of Mei Tenggen, the director of Hangzhou Guangji Hospital (now the Second Affiliated Hospital of Zhejiang University Medical College) , bowing to a patient, also known as "across the hundred years, " the doctor-patient mutual respect photos.

”

On February 23,2020, a picture of a 3-year-old boy bowing to medical staff was released by Xinhua News Agency's@xinhua viewpoint.

On Feb. 22, a 3-year-old patient in the isolation ward of Shaoxing City Center Hospital in Zhejiang Province was photographed as he emerged from the hospital and bowed to his aunt, according to Xinhua News Agency. It is reported that the small patient has fever symptoms, nucleic acid test was negative, cured after discharge.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On his release from the hospital, the boy thanked his "nurse Mother" several times for taking good care of him, according to the Yue Niu News Service in Shaoxing. Before they parted, Zézé made a sudden bow to the nurse, who was so moved by the child's loveliness and sincerity that she stooped down to bow her thanks. And this touching scene was just recorded by a passing colleague.

However, interface news noted that there are also users of Shaoxing Central Hospital for this photo issued a different voice, that there is suspected of posing. "The news picture is about the reality of time. Does a three-year-old really have such a high level of culture and understanding of life? " One Netizen questioned.

@ Xinhua view said the photos were provided by Shaoxing Central Hospital in Zhejiang Province. On the morning of February 24, the Shaoxing Central Hospital responded to interface news that the photo had been obtained by accident and that no photographer or other adult had instructed the boy to bow.

According to the hospital office staff, the day the boy was discharged, the hospital held a send-off ceremony. The nurse who took care of the boy played with him while he waited for his parents to pick him up.

Because the farewell ceremony needed photos, someone was in charge of taking photos at the scene, so when the little boy made the sudden gesture of bowing, he was just photographed, "only his grandparents were with him at the time, so there was no possibility of being forced by his parents, as netizens suspected. "

The hospital did not disclose the details of the boy and his family. "originally, we only passed it around among our doctor friends, and it may have been noticed by the media and reporters, and then the picture was taken away, but it went viral on the Internet, " said the hospital's office staff.
